You are in a Living Room.
Your living room a pretty messy room, probably the worst. Your couch is ruined, by moths. Funny, just yesterday it was fine. You're starting to get kind of pissed, but also curious. Your TV is broken, the screen smashed, and your movie shelf is knocked over, movie cases all over the floor. The family chest is the only thing in here that is still where it was yesterday. Your mom told you when you turned 18 and moved out, not to open it until the time came. She said you'd know when it was time. Right now seems like a good time, but maybe not. You wonder what's inside. You are also starting to wonder what the spell pages are for, and why they seem to perform miracles. You remember something your mom had said about magic before you left to live on your own. You don't remember much, probably because you were too busy thinking about what you were gonna do, where you wanted to live. To the north is your front door.
